## PART 5: DEVELOPMENT PHASES & PRIORITIES

### Phase 1: Foundation & Setup (Weeks 1-2) - CRITICAL

**Priority 1 - Must Have:**
- Next.js 14+ project setup with TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS configured with custom dark theme color palette
- Git repository with branching strategy
- Project folder structure: /app, /components, /lib, /public, /styles
- Design tokens as CSS variables in globals.css
- Storybook setup for component documentation
- ESLint and Prettier configuration

**Priority 2 - Essential:**
- Core component library:
  - Button (all variants: primary, secondary, icon, sizes)
  - Form inputs (text, select, checkbox, radio)
  - Card component (product, content variants)
  - Modal/Dialog
  - Navigation bar skeleton
  - Toast notifications
- Responsive grid system (12-column grid)
- Breakpoint system: sm (640px), md (768px), lg (1024px), xl (1280px)

**Priority 3 - Important:**
- Lucide React icons integration
- Shadow and animation utilities
- Color palette testing in Storybook
- Accessibility setup (WCAG guidelines)

**Testing:**
- Visual regression tests for components
- Responsive design tests across breakpoints
- Color contrast verification tool

### Phase 2: Product Catalog & E-Commerce (Weeks 3-6) - CORE FUNCTIONALITY

**Week 3: Database & Backend API**

Priority 1 - Must Have:
- Database schema design:
  - Products collection: name, description, price, brand, images, frames (type, material, color), suitable_face_shapes, lens_types, features
  - Users collection: email, password (hashed), profile, addresses, preferences
  - Orders collection: order_id, user_id, items, total, status, shipping_address, payment_info
  - Reviews collection: product_id, user_id, rating, title, content, images, helpful_count
- Image storage: Cloudinary or AWS S3
- Seed data: Minimum 500 eyewear products with varied attributes
- CRUD API routes for products

Priority 2 - Essential:
- User authentication API (sign up, login, logout, JWT tokens)
- Product filtering logic backend
- Search implementation with full-text indexing
- Database indexes for performance

**Week 4: Home Page & Product Pages**

Priority 1 - Must Have:
- Home page as specified in Part 3 (all sections)
- Product catalog page with grid layout
- Product detail page with all information
- Navigation bar fully functional
- Footer with all sections

Priority 2 - Essential:
- Hero section animations
- Category grid with hover effects
- Best sellers carousel
- Responsive design for all pages
- Image optimization and lazy loading

**Week 5: Search & Filtering**

Priority 1 - Must Have:
- Search functionality (debounced, real-time)
- All filter types working (gender, material, color, face shape, price, brand)
- Sort functionality (price, popularity, rating, newest)
- Filter tags display and removal
