## PART 6: TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS & CONSTRAINTS

### Technology Stack

**Frontend:**
- React 18+ (latest stable)
- Next.js 14+ (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS (with custom configuration)
- Lucide React for icons
- Framer Motion for animations (optional but recommended)

**Backend:**
- Node.js (latest LTS)
- Next.js API routes
- MongoDB or PostgreSQL
- JWT for authentication
- Bcryptjs for password hashing

**Third-Party Services:**
- Razorpay for payments
- Google Maps API for doctor finder
- Cloudinary or AWS S3 for images
- MediaPipe for face detection (client-side)
- TensorFlow.js for any ML features
- Sentry for error tracking
- Google Analytics 4 for analytics

**DevOps:**
- Git for version control
- GitHub or GitLab for repository
- Vercel or Netlify for deployment
- GitHub Actions for CI/CD
- Docker for containerization (optional)

### Browser Support

- Chrome (latest 2 versions)
- Firefox (latest 2 versions)
- Safari (latest 2 versions, both desktop and iOS)
- Edge (latest 2 versions)
- Mobile browsers (Chrome, Safari iOS)

### Performance Targets

- Lighthouse Score: >90
- First Contentful Paint (FCP): <1.5 seconds
- Largest Contentful Paint (LCP): <2.5 seconds
- Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS): <0.1
- Time to Interactive (TTI): <3.5 seconds
- Mobile performance score: >85

### Security Requirements

- SSL/TLS encryption for all data in transit
- HTTPS only (never HTTP)
- CSRF protection on all forms
- XSS prevention (sanitize user inputs)
- SQL injection prevention (parameterized queries)
- Rate limiting on API endpoints
- Authentication on protected routes
- Authorization checks on backend
- Regular security audits
- Password hashing with bcryptjs (minimum 10 rounds)
- JWT token expiration (7 days)
- Secure cookie settings (httpOnly, secure, sameSite)
- No sensitive data in localStorage (use secure cookies)

### Accessibility Requirements (WCAG 2.1 AA)

- Keyboard navigation: All interactive elements reachable via Tab key
- Focus indicators: Visible focus state on all interactive elements
- Color contrast: 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- Alt text: All images must have descriptive alt text
- ARIA labels: Form inputs, buttons, icons must have aria-label or aria-labelledby
- Semantic HTML: Use proper semantic tags (button, nav, main, section, etc.)
- Skip links: "Skip to main content" link
- Error messages: Clear, accessible error messaging
- Focus management: Modals trap focus appropriately

---

## PART 7: DATA STRUCTURE & API DESIGN

### Key Collections/Tables

**Products:**
```
{
  id, name, description, brand, price, images[], 
  frameType, material, color, suitableFaceShapes, 
  lensTypes, features, coatings, rating, reviewCount, 
  inStock, quantity, createdAt, updatedAt
}
```

**Users:**
```
{
  id, email, password, name, profile{}, 
  addresses[], preferences, wishlist[], 
  createdAt, updatedAt, lastLogin
}
```

**Orders:**
```
{
  id, userId, items[], subtotal, discount, tax, total, 
  shippingAddress, billingAddress, paymentMethod, 
  paymentStatus, orderStatus, tracking, createdAt
}
```

**Reviews:**
```
{
  id, productId, userId, rating, title, content, 
  images[], helpful, notHelpful, createdAt
}
```

### API Response Format

All API responses should follow this format:
```
{
  success: boolean,
  data: any,
  message: string,
  error: string (if applicable),
  timestamp: ISO string
}
```

### Error Handling

- All errors should return appropriate HTTP status codes (400, 401, 403, 404, 500, etc.)
- Include descriptive error messages
- Log errors server-side for debugging
- Show user-friendly error messages on frontend
- Implement retry logic for failed requests

